vim 'filename': create a new file and edit
# Under vim
esc: exit the editing mode, change to command mode
# After 'esc'
:w: save the edited conten, not exit the vim editor
:wq: save and quit
:wq!: save and quit forcefully (when there is no writing permissions)
:q: quit the editor (only when not editing the file)
:q!: quit the editor and not save the edited file
:w 'filename': save the edited file to 'filename'
:w! 'filename': same as above, if 'filename' exists, substitute it
:wq! 'filename': same as the above, then quit
